column5: I'll bet the guy in the tree stand is thankful that was a black bear. If it had been a grizzly or brown, when he said "What are you doin there" the answer probably would ahve been "I'm fixin to have lunch!
I'm surprised he waited that long to make a noise. First paw on the rung he'd be hearing about it
First paw on the rung  , it would know by the stinky brown rain falling on his/her head , down the leg and in the boot ... lmao
